text:
Hey <!channel>
I wanted to ask you not to add me to any new board in Miro.
I have a free plan and I can only use 3 boards, I have already reached the maximum :pensive:
If you invite me to a new board, Miro automatically adds me and there is no way to decline the invitation or leave it.
This means that I can no longer modify one of the other boards I am working for different projects.
At the moment I made the Lefthoek board you shared with me primary :+1:
But I can't add another one in the future.

(Unless we get rich and take a paid plan, Miro has a big discount for start-ups, if I remember correctly :sunglasses:)
